e%2C%20the%20former%20commander%20of%20U.S.%20Naval%20Forces%20Europe%20and%20Africa%2C%20was%20charged%20by%20federal%20prosecutions%20in%20a%20bribery%20case.%3Cp%3EMC1%20(SW%2FAW)%20Fred%20Gray%20IV%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20former%20top%20Navy%20admiral%20was%20arrested%20Friday%20on%20charges%20related%20to%20a%20bribery%20scheme.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20alleges%20Burke%20accepted%20bribes%20to%20steer%20work%20towards%20a%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBurke%20is%20a%20retired%20four-star%20and%20the%20former%20vice%20chief%20of%20naval%20operations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20retired%20top%20US%20Navy%20admiral%20who%20briefly%20served%20as%20the%20second%20highest-ranking%20Navy%20officer%20was%20arrested%20Friday%20on%20federal%20charges%20related%20to%20a%20bribery%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fpr%2Fretired-navy-admiral-and-business-executives-arrested-bribery-scheme%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E%20alleged%20that%20from%202020%20to%202022%2C%20then-Adm.%20Robert%20Burke%20accepted%20bribes%20to%20help%20a%20training%20firm%20win%20certain%20contracts%20while%20he%20was%20commanding%20US%20Naval%20Forces%20Europe%20and%20Africa%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20high-paying%20job%20as%20soon%20as%20he%20retired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20said%20that%20Burke%2C%20a%20former%20four-star%2C%20used%20%26quot%3Bhis%20official%20position%20to%20influence%20other%20Navy%20officers%20to%20award%20another%20contract%20to%20Company%20A%20to%20train%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20the%20Navy%20with%20a%20value%20%5Bthe%20contractors%5D%20allegedly%20estimated%20to%20be%20'triple%20digit%20millions.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20had%20previously%20had%20a%20contract%20with%20the%20Navy%20to%20provide%20a%20workforce%20training%20pilot%20program%20from%20August%202018%20to%20July%202019%20before%20it%20was%20then%20terminated%20in%20late%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20company%20remains%20unnamed%20in%20the%20DOJ%20release%2C%20Yongchul%20%26quot%3BCharlie%26quot%3B%20Kim%20and%20Meghan%20Messenger%20are%20named%20as%20the%20two%20other%20co-defendants%20in%20the%20case%20and%20identified%20as%20co-CEOs%20of%20the%20company.%20Kim%20and%20Messenger%20are%20listed%20as%20co-CEOs%20on%20the%20site%20of%20company%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnextjump.com%2Fleadership%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENextJump%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurke%2C%20the%20indictment%20said%2C%20is%20alleged%20to%20have%20ordered%20his%20staff%20to%20award%20a%20contract%20to%20the%20company%20to%20train%20personnel%20directly%20under%20his%20command%20in%20Italy%20and%20Spain%20in%20December%202021.%20The%20contract's%20cost%20was%20%24355%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Burke%20retired%20from%20the%20Navy%20in%20October%202022%2C%20he%20began%20working%20at%20the%20company%20with%20a%20yearly%20starting%20salary%20of%20%24500%2C000%2C%20the%20indictment%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDOJ%20also%20noted%20that%20Burke%20purportedly%20lied%20to%20the%20Navy%20about%20this%20employment%20and%20his%20relationship%20with%20the%20company%2C%20writing%3A%20%26quot%3BTo%20conceal%20the%20scheme%2C%20Burke%20allegedly%20made%20several%20false%20and%20misleading%20statements%20to%20the%20Navy%2C%20including%20by%20creating%20the%20false%20appearance%20that%20Burke%20played%20no%20role%20in%20issuing%20the%20contract%20and%20falsely%20implying%20that%20Company%20A's%20employment%20discussions%20with%20Burke%20only%20began%20months%20after%20the%20contract%20was%20awarded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurke%2C%20Kim%20and%20Messenger%20did%20not%20immediately%20reply%20to%20a%20message%20from%20BI%20seeking%20comment%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurke%20was%20the%20Navy's%20highest%20ranking%20officer%20in%20Europe%20from%20July%202020%20to%202022.%20Prior%20to%20that