and%20hospitals%20to%20create%20special%20units%20to%20treat%20heat-related%20illnesses%2C%20while%20workers%20on%20construction%20sites%20were%20given%20a%20%26quot%3Bpaid%20holiday%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20look%20at%20what%20caused%20the%20unprecedented%20heat%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHOW%20UNUSUAL%20HAS%20THE%20SITUATION%20BEEN%20THIS%20YEAR%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20every%20year%20temperatures%20in%20India%20tend%20to%20peak%20in%20the%20months%20of%20May%20and%20June%2C%20the%20number%20of%20heatwave%20days%20recorded%20over%20northwestern%20and%20eastern%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20this%20season%20have%20been%20more%20than%20double%20the%20normal%2C%20with%20eastern%20India%20also%20experiencing%20its%20hottest%20April%20on%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20declares%20a%20heatwave%20day%20when%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20in%20any%20given%20region%20is%204.5%20-6.4%20degrees%20Celsius%20higher%20than%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParts%20of%20the%20country%20have%20touched%20new%20highs%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20maximum%20temperature%2C%20including%20Delhi%2C%20which%20recorded%20the%20country's%20highest%20ever%20temperature%20at%2052.9%20C%20(127.22%20degree%20F)%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20figure%20may%20be%20revised%20as%20officials%20are%20investigating%20whether%20it%20was%20caused%20by%20an%20error%20in%20the%20sensor%2C%20two%20areas%20in%20Delhi%20also%20recorded%2049.9%20C%20a%20day%20earlier%20-%20an%20all-time%20high%20for%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20northern%20Haryana%20state%2C%20which%20surrounds%20Delhi%20from%20three%20sides%2C%20the%20Rohtak%20region%20recorded%20its%20highest-ever%20temperature%20on%20Friday%20at%2047.5%20C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHY%20HAVE%20TEMPERATURES%20RISEN%20THIS%20SEASON%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20from%20India's%20weather%20department%20said%20that%20while%20a%20rise%20in%20temperatures%20during%20May%20and%20June%20is%20normal%2C%20it%20is%20usually%20controlled%20by%20periodic%20western%20disturbances%2C%20which%20are%20weather%20systems%20originating%20in%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea%20that%20bring%20moisture-laden%20winds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20neutralise%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20hot%2C%20dry%20air%20coming%20from%20the%20direction%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20Afghanistan%20into%20northern%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20however%2C%20there%20were%20more%20western%20disturbances%20between%20March%20and%20early%20May%20than%20usual%2C%20while%20their%20strength%20has%20reduced%20over%20the%20last%20%26quot%3B10-15%20days%26quot%3B%2C%20leaving%20the%20wind%20coming%20from%20neighbouring%20countries%20unchecked%20and%20causing%20temperatures%20to%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobal%20and%20India-based%20experts%20say%20such%20weather%20changes%20are%20being%20worsened%20by%20human-driven%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHY%20IS%20THE%20SITUATION%20IN%20DELHI%20PARTICULARLY%20BAD%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESurrounded%20by%20alluvial%20plains%20in%20the%20north%20and%20east%2C%20the%20Thar%20desert%20in%20the%20west%2C%20and%20the%20Aravalli%20hill%20ranges%20in%20the%20south%2C%20Delhi%2C%20with%20a%20population%20of%20about%2020%20million%2C%20is%20one%20of%20India's%20fastest-growing%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20and%20experts%20say%20apart%20from%20its%20location%2C%20the%20capital%20is%20also%20particularly%20vulnerable%20because%20of%20its%20large%20population%2C%20scattered%20vegetation%2C%20and%20increased%20construction%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades%2C%20with%20the%20built-up%20area%20increasing%20from%2031.4%25%20in%202003%20to%20more%20than%2038%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHEN%20WILL%20THE%20HEAT%20ABATE%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%2C%20the%20temperature%20in%20northwest%2C%20central%2C%20and%20east%20India%20will%20gradually%20decline%20over%20the%20next%20three%20days%20because%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20approaching%20western%20disturbance%2C%20rainfall%2C%20and%20the%20southwesterly%20wind%20blowing%20from%20the%20Arabian%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonsoon%20rains%20reached%20the%20southernmost%20state%20of%20Kerala%20on%20Thursday%2C%20bringing%20relief%20to%20residents%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717175760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F6013gjj_delhi-heat-reuters_625x300_31_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-why-have-temperatures-reached-record-highs-in-india-5789289%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Several%20parts%20of%20India%20grappled%20with%20unusually%20high%20temperatures%20this%20week%2C%20forcing%20schools%20to%20close%20and%20hospitals%20to%20create%20special%20units%20to%20treat%20heat-related%20illnesses%2C%20while%20workers%20on%20construction%20sites%20were%20given%20a%20%26quot%3Bpaid%20holiday%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20afterno%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-why-have-temperatures-reached-record-highs-in-india-5789289%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-why-have-temperatures-reached-record-highs-in-india-5789289%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-why-have-temperatures-reached-record-highs-in-india-5789289%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Udupi%20Cochin%20Shipyard%20bags%20new%20order%20from%20Adani%20group's%20Ocean%20Sparkle%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717175204